# CodeCortex subagents

Delegate via **Task** for long or isolated chains (10+ MCP calls).

| Intent | Subagent / tool |
| --- | --- |
| Stale index / setup / watch | `codecortex-indexer` |
| Callers, impact, dead code, search | `codecortex-analyzer` |
| Branch or PR review | `codecortex-pr-reviewer` |
| Plan edit (read-only) | `codecortex-patch-planner` |
| Multi-step PR / kernel / consensus review | [`cortex_a2a_spawn_session`](../../docs/A2A.md) — prefer before Task subagent MCP chains |

For PR review, kernel/eBPF impact, deadlock consensus, and other multi-step orchestration, spawn an A2A session once and poll the returned `task_id` instead of chaining 10+ MCP tools in the host context. See [codecortex-a2a.mdc](codecortex-a2a.mdc) and [docs/A2A.md](../../docs/A2A.md).

## Order

Run **codecortex-indexer** before analyzer/reviewer/planner when `freshness` is not fresh.

Parent agent implements code; **codecortex-patch-planner** does not write files.

